634	    /// Performs a bitwise "and" operation on the current tag and the argument `val`, and sets the
635	    /// new tag to the result. Returns the previous pointer.
636	    ///
637	    /// This method takes an [`Ordering`] argument which describes the memory ordering of this
638	    /// operation.
639	    ///
640	    /// # Examples
641	    ///
642	    /// ```
